  "issue_number": 123,
  "issue_title": "feature: add running agent state controls",
  "issue_body": "## Problem\n\nUsers need clear control while a local multi-step task is running. Without visible run state and cancellation, the app can feel stuck or unsafe during longer tasks.\n\n## Proposed behavior\n\nAdd running-state UI for local agent runs. The chat screen should show whether the run is idle, running, waiting for approval, waiting for clarification, completed, failed, blocked, or cancelled. Add a cancel/stop control for active runs.\n\n## User workflow\n\nThe user starts a task, sees that TouchPilot is running, and can stop it before more actions execute.\n\n## Local-first impact\n\nThis keeps local automation user-directed and inspectable.\n\n## Safety and security considerations\n\nCancel must stop future actions cleanly. It should not interrupt an already-dispatched Android action in a way that leaves internal state inconsistent.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- Chat screen shows clear run state.\n- Active runs have a stop/cancel action.\n- Completed, failed, blocked, and cancelled states are visually distinct.\n- Cancelled runs emit a stop step/reason.\n- Includes UI-level tests or focused state tests where practical.",
